Name: Fran
Description: One of CrossFit's original benchmark Girl workouts created by Greg Glassman to test metabolic conditioning via thrusters and pull-ups.
Flavor_Text: Fran - A very high intensity lactate threshold (anaerobic) challenge that demands focus and grit.
CoachNotes: Go unbroken if possible; keep transitions tight; control breathing.
Warmup: 5-10m 0s general cardio (row/jog/bike); Air squats and goblet squats progression, ankle mobility; Scapular pull-ups, ring rows or banded pull-ups

Scaling_Tiers.Beginner: Complete 10-7-4 reps of Thrusters and Pull-ups. - Beginner: lighter loads, banded/assistance, reduced volume.
Scaling_Tiers.Intermediate: Complete 21-15-9 reps of Thrusters and Pull-ups. - Intermediate: moderate loads, standard scaling.
Scaling_Tiers.Advanced: Complete 21-15-9 reps of Thrusters and Pull-ups. - Advanced: Rx or add weight/tempo.
Scaling_Tiers.Limited Equipment: Complete 21-15-9 reps of Thrusters and Pull-ups. - Limited equipment: substitute barbells with dumbbells/kettlebells, row with running.

TargetStimulus: High-intensity sprint with pulling and barbell cycling.
Instructions: complete 21-15-9 reps of thrusters and pull-ups.
Instructions_Clean: complete 21-15-9 repetitions of thrusters and pull-ups.
ScalingOptions: Reduce reps, lighten load, or modify gymnastics (e.g., banded pull-ups, lighter KB, shortened run distances).
Coaching_Cues: Pace the workout according to the time domain; avoid all-out opening bursts unless short sprint. Break thrusters into manageable sets; keep front rack tight. Use kip efficiently; consider banded pull-ups to keep turnover high.
